1 Doll ars ($1000.00) for the first hour and Two Hundred Fifty Dollars
2 ($250.00) for each additional quarter hour. The cost to replace
3 Class A firefighting foam used to extinguish a fire may be added to
4 the fire department response fee. This rate shall be reviewed
5 annually by the Insurance Commissioner of the Oklahoma Insurance
6 Department, and any increase amounts will be determined by either
7 the Consumer Price Index or an alternative index the Commissioner
8 deems appropriate. For purposes of this section, "consumer price
9 index" means the consumer price index for all urban consumers as
10 determined by the Bureau of Labor Statistics within the United
11 States Department of Labor.
12 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6093 of Title 36, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 In rural fire departments, coverage for a fire department
16 response to a motor vehicle accident shall be provided under the
17 liability coverage policy. The coverage shall be for a fire
18 department response at a rate of Five Hundred Forty Dollars
19 ($540.00) per hour for the first hour and One Hundred Thirty-five
20 Dollars ($135.00) for each additional quarter hour. If powered
21 rescue equipment is used to extricate a victim or victims, the total
22 amount will be increased by twenty-five percent (25%). An
23 additional fee to cover the cost of replacing absorbent materials
24 such as oil dry, absorbent pads and booms may also be charged. This
